{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f03d9e6f-fe2a-47fd-a791-9bbe08b3eec0","content":"Yes, you'll run into compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2 and .NET Core 3.1**, but it **dropped support for `net5.0`** since .NET 5 is out of support.\n\nHere's the breakdown for your target frameworks:\n\n| Framework | MSTest v3 Compatible? |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Yes |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ⚠️ Builds, but .NET Core 3.1 is end-of-life |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ No — not supported |\n\n**Recommended actions before migrating:**\n\n1. Replace `net5.0` with `net6.0` or `net8.0` (currently supported .NET versions).\n2. Consider replacing `netcoreapp3.1` as well, since it's also out of support.\n3. Then update MSTest packages to v3 (`MSTest.TestFramework` / `MSTest.TestAdapter` 3.x), or switch to the unified `MSTest` meta-package.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f4172d04-546f-4579-988b-a63a223181ca","outputTokens":280,"requestId":"A411:1FB426:14E0605:1672073:6A02EC52"},"id":"6684dbb7-f1d2-4084-957f-e439d0be7732","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:01:16.975Z","parentId":"d99db128-2e1d-4c27-a359-27d3d0508d08"}
